{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:47.469874+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 89f0a7baf98809d58ba801b27cefdcec95f52467)", "id": "lc_0ed56858-7ff0-471c-9965-b41f43f8ef14"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\nfor f in seeds/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Seeding from $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_a0dbb8c1-81be-4186-ba7c-af96aa41012d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "45fdc441-c62d-46f7-a272-1db8b7e5ee2c", "tool_call_id": "call_02_6L5ZfS8WV0VTnc5T2nxd9579", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:47.475662+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_1938e355-e85b-41c2-83b1-a49137efda69"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_b309aef5-4c09-4255-ace1-c821ef477149"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d83faa0b-7e41-4f62-ade1-2c1ac71def85", "tool_call_id": "call_01_6XmeqIXjib0R00fOJckm1593", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:47.658571+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 191a325f70d374d1dbb3302d95de9165897f2562)", "id": "lc_0fdae5c0-0bc3-4623-ac7f-53f30154d44e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "INSERT INTO users (email, display_name) VALUES\n    ('admin@local', 'Local Admin'),\n    ('alice@local', 'Alice (dev)'),\n    ('bob@local',   'Bob (dev)');\n", "id": "lc_1dec71f1-778c-4db2-9783-a249a4062c94"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d737d20e-0850-4178-9639-9cb86d13bb4e", "tool_call_id": "call_00_ifV46M3uBcIcMoACTCFe8268", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:50.413945+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 189, "prompt_tokens": 8676, "total_tokens": 8865, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8192}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8192, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 484}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "021fe88a-49ec-4ffa-9825-c754ff7c3b13", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e7-082b-7723-950b-c7d087eaa891-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01_C02_A02", "path": "docs/operations.md"}, "id": "call_00_e5aH52VzEFP3E11rfpYi1805", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01_C02_A02", "path": "README.md"}, "id": "call_01_Ul6hFdDnO4XbiTmUiL9Y7136", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8676, "output_tokens": 189, "total_tokens": 8865, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8192}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 23}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:51.152986+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 503da61487c44c4a9f754b83f8dbf5ee1efdfb61)", "id": "lc_6d85b2d0-8825-4138-834b-f50c58026f28"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# pgdev — local PostgreSQL dev scaffold\n\nA minimal, opinionated PostgreSQL setup for local development. **Not** for\nproduction. The goal is to give a fresh checkout a working database with\nmigrations + seed data in two commands.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Docker + docker compose v2\n\n## Quickstart\n\n```\ncp .env.example .env\ndocker compose up -d\n./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n./scripts/seed.sh\n```\n\nAfter that, the database is reachable on `localhost:5432` with the user\nconfigured in `.env` (default `app` / `app`).\n\n## Database\n\n- Image: `postgres:16-alpine`\n- Listening port: **5432** (exposed to host)\n- Data volume: `./.pgdata` (gitignored)\n- Logging: configured in `config/postgresql.conf` (default: `log_statement = 'ddl'`)\n- Auth: configured in `config/pg_hba.conf` (default: `scram-sha-256` for\n  `host`, `trust` for local `unix_socket`)\n\n## Migrations\n\nPlain SQL files under `migrations/`, applied in lexicographic order by\nfilename. Use the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n\nThe current set:\n\n| File                        | Purpose                                |\n|-----------------------------|----------------------------------------|\n| `001_create_users.sql`      | Create `users` table.                  |\n| `002_create_sessions.sql`   | Create `sessions` table, FK to users.  |\n| `003_add_session_index.sql` | Add `idx_sessions_user_id` on sessions.|\n\n## Seeds\n\nPlain SQL files under `seeds/`, applied after migrations. See `seeds/README.md`.\n\n## Operations\n\nSee [`docs/operations.md`](docs/operations.md) for resetting, backups, and\ncommon troubleshooting.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_50d35fba-af8f-4760-946b-cda8406a12d3"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "a5791176-7f9d-42b6-af5c-3e05b11beea0", "tool_call_id": "call_01_Ul6hFdDnO4XbiTmUiL9Y7136", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:51.222387+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 100cb750df504bd244d316a7ebbaea30052af7b1)", "id": "lc_07696b6e-a6f9-46d0-82b7-758a5a35b4c7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Operations\n\n## Reset\n\n```\n./scripts/reset.sh\n```\n\nWipes `.pgdata`, recreates the container, re-applies all migrations + seeds.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### \"could not connect\" from outside Docker\n\nConfirm the container is up: `docker ps | grep pgdev_db`. Confirm port\nforwarding: `docker compose port db 5432`. Default exposed port is `5432`.\n\n### Logs\n\n```\ndocker compose logs -f db\n```\n\n`log_statement = 'ddl'` is set by default, so DDL is logged but DML is not.\nBump to `'all'` in `config/postgresql.conf` if you need full query logs.\n\n### Migration ordering\n\n`apply_migrations.sh` relies on shell glob lexicographic ordering. Keep\nthe `NNN_description.sql` convention so `010_*.sql` and `100_*.sql` sort\ncorrectly.\n", "id": "lc_0cbc7ae8-111c-4705-b69c-b8bea85f058d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0de4ba2c-cef2-4daf-b3fc-deaacc86edac", "tool_call_id": "call_00_e5aH52VzEFP3E11rfpYi1805", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
