{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:05:20.190243+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1571, "prompt_tokens": 10789, "total_tokens": 12360, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 1173, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10368}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10368, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 421}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "a0d49a6e-ba87-476c-bc3c-d1cd7a105f91", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e7-3ff4-71c3-a96c-8fb01ff02d54-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "pull_request_review_write", "args": {"method": "create", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01_C02_A02", "pullNumber": 2, "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES", "body": "Thanks for this cleanup — the migration itself is sound and safe (`DROP TABLE IF EXISTS` is the right call for an empty legacy table with no dependencies). I also appreciate the staging verification noted in the comment.\n\nBefore merge, there are two things to address:\n\n### 1. README migration table is out of date (blocking)\n\nThe README explicitly lists every migration in a table. Right now it stops at `003`. Once `004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` lands, the table drifts from the actual migration set. The DBA review comment flagged this too. Please add a row, e.g.:\n\n```\n| `004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` | Drop legacy `sessions_v1` table. |\n```\n\nKeeping that table accurate matters for onboarding — it's the first place someone looks to understand the schema evolution.\n\n### 2. Missing trailing newline (nice-to-have)\n\n`migrations/004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` has no trailing newline. Not critical, but it's a standard convention (POSIX line definition, git diffs, some editors). Consider appending one.\n\nOnce those are addressed (at minimum #1), this is good to merge."}, "id": "call_00_87tpuWa7tJ8WIMorVQVy1603", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10789, "output_tokens": 1571, "total_tokens": 12360, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10368}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 1173}}}}]}}}
